Q12: Who is likely to pay back? Who is not likely to pay back?¶

Duration -0.21, Amount -0.15, Real Estate 0.12, Prop unknown -0.13, Check account 0 -0.26, check account 3 0.32, History 0 -0.14, History 1 -0.13, History 4 0.18, Savings account 4 0.13, Employment 1 -0.11,

From the data visualizations I have created, I found that Duration, Check account, History, Amount, Real Estate, Savings account, and employment seem to be the variables that affect RESPONSE the most.

Those with credit history of existing credits paid back duly till now, delay in paying off, were the least likely ones who paid back their loan. However, those who had critical accounts seemed to pay off most of the time. Not suprisingly, those who had to pay back higher amounts were more likely to default on their loan payment. Also, those who have been employed for less than a year were not very good at paying back their loans.

Those who owned real estate were likely to pay back their loan as they would be able to earn money consistently that way. In addition, those with large amounts of money in their savings account were able to pay back on their loans around 80% of the time.

Other variables in the dataset were not seen as significant in determining the RESPONSE variable, and focusing on these things: the length of the time to pay back the loan, the amount of the loan, current balance in account, their credit history, and their checking account status, it is possible to determine who will pay back their loan or not.
